```javascript
// .husky/pre-commit
#!/bin/sh
. "$(dirname "$0")/_/husky.sh"

echo "Running pre-commit security checks..."

# Check for vulnerabilities before committing
npm audit --audit-level=high
if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  echo "ERROR: High severity vulnerabilities detected!"
  echo "Run 'npm audit fix' or review and address vulnerabilities."
  exit 1
fi

echo "Security checks passed!"
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Pre-commit hooks**: Block commits with high-severity vulnerabilities
```javascript
// Enforce in git hooks
const auditResult = execSync('npm audit --json');
const parsed = JSON.parse(auditResult);
if (parsed.metadata.vulnerabilities.high > 0) {
  process.exit(1);
}
```

2. **CI/CD pipeline gates**: Fail builds on vulnerability detection
```yaml
- name: Security gate
  run: |
    npm audit --audit-level=moderate
    if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
      echo "::error::Security vulnerabilities detected"
      exit 1
    fi
```

3. **Continuous monitoring**: Scheduled scans and alerts
```javascript
// Monitor for new vulnerabilities in deployed apps
const schedule = require('node-schedule');
schedule.scheduleJob('0 */6 * * *', async () => {
  const scanner = new DependencyScanner();
  const results = await scanner.scan();
  if (results.overallStatus === 'fail') {
    await sendSlackAlert(results);
  }
});
```

**Additional Protections**:
- **Lock file integrity**: Use `npm ci` instead of `npm install` in CI to ensure reproducible builds from package-lock.json
- **Software Bill of Materials (SBOM)**: Generate CycloneDX or SPDX SBOMs for supply chain transparency
- **Dependency pinning**: Use exact versions in production, ranges only in development
- **Private registry scanning**: If using npm Enterprise or Artifactory, enable vulnerability scanning on package ingestion
- **Renovate/Dependabot**: Automate dependency update PRs with security priority
- **Runtime monitoring**: Use tools like Snyk Runtime Protection to detect exploitation attempts in production

Transitive dependencies are the hidden attack surface - Log4Shell affected applications through dozens of intermediate libraries. Production-grade dependency security requires continuous monitoring and rapid response capabilities.

**PRODUCTION PATTERN**:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>

    <groupId>com.enterprise</groupId>
    <artifactId>secure-enterprise-app</artifactId>
    <version>2.0.0</version>
    <packaging>jar</packaging>

    <parent>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
        <version>3.2.1</version>
        <relativePath/>
    </parent>

    <properties>
        <java.version>21</java.version>
        <!-- Centralized version management for security-critical deps -->
        <log4j2.version>2.22.1</log4j2.version>
        <jackson.version>2.16.1</jackson.version>
        <snakeyaml.version>2.2</snakeyaml.version>
        <commons-text.version>1.11.0</commons-text.version>
    </properties>

    <dependencyManagement>
        <dependencies>
            <!-- Force safe versions of transitive dependencies -->
            <dependency>
                <groupId>org.apache.logging.log4j</groupId>
                <artifactId>log4j-bom</artifactId>
                <version>${log4j2.version}</version>
                <type>pom</type>
                <scope>import</scope>
            </dependency>

            <!-- Override vulnerable SnakeYAML (CVE-2022-1471) -->
            <dependency>
                <groupId>org.yaml</groupId>
                <artifactId>snakeyaml</artifactId>
                <version>${snakeyaml.version}</version>
            </dependency>

            <!-- Override vulnerable Jackson (CVE-2020-36518) -->
            <dependency>
                <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson</groupId>
                <artifactId>jackson-bom</artifactId>
                <version>${jackson.version}</version>
                <type>pom</type>
                <scope>import</scope>
            </dependency>

            <!-- Override vulnerable commons-text (CVE-2022-42889) -->
            <dependency>
                <groupId>org.apache.commons</groupId>
                <artifactId>commons-text</artifactId>
                <version>${commons-text.version}</version>
            </dependency>
        </dependencies>
    </dependencyManagement>

    <dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
            <exclusions>
                <!-- Exclude unused dependencies to reduce attack surface -->
                <exclusion>
                    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
                    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-tomcat</artifactId>
                </exclusion>
            </exclusions>
        </dependency>

        <!-- Use Undertow instead of Tomcat for reduced attack surface -->
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-undertow</artifactId>
        </dependency>

        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-actuator</artifactId>
        </dependency>
    </dependencies>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <!-- OWASP Dependency Check with NVD API key for better rate limits -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.owasp</groupId>
                <artifactId>dependency-check-maven</artifactId>
                <version>9.0.7</version>
                <configuration>
                    <failBuildOnCVSS>7</failBuildOnCVSS>
                    <nvdApiKey>${env.NVD_API_KEY}</nvdApiKey>
                    <formats>
                        <format>HTML</format>
                        <format>JSON</format>
                        <format>SARIF</format>
                    </formats>
                    <suppressionFiles>
                        <suppressionFile>dependency-check-suppressions.xml</suppressionFile>
                    </suppressionFiles>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>

            <!-- Versions Maven Plugin for update detection -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.codehaus.mojo</groupId>
                <artifactId>versions-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>2.16.2</version>
                <configuration>
                    <rulesUri>file:///${project.basedir}/version-rules.xml</rulesUri>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>

            <!-- Enforcer Plugin to ban vulnerable dependencies -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
                <artifactId>maven-enforcer-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>3.4.1</version>
                <executions>
                    <execution>
                        <id>ban-vulnerable-dependencies</id>
                        <goals>
                            <goal>enforce</goal>
                        </goals>
                        <configuration>
                            <rules>
                                <bannedDependencies>
                                    <excludes>
                                        <!-- Ban known vulnerable versions -->
                                        <exclude>org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-core:[,2.17.0)</exclude>
                                        <exclude>org.yaml:snakeyaml:[,2.0)</exclude>
                                        <exclude>com.fasterxml.jackson.core:*:[,2.13.4)</exclude>
                                        <exclude>org.apache.commons:commons-text:[,1.10.0)</exclude>
                                        <exclude>ch.qos.logback:logback-core:[,1.4.12)</exclude>
                                    </excludes>
                                </bannedDependencies>
                                <requireUpperBoundDeps/>
                            </rules>
                        </configuration>
                    </execution>
                </executions>
            </plugin>

            <!-- CycloneDX SBOM Generator -->
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.cyclonedx</groupId>
                <artifactId>cyclonedx-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>2.7.11</version>
                <executions>
                    <execution>
                        <phase>package</phase>
                        <goals>
                            <goal>makeAggregateBom</goal>
                        </goals>
                    </execution>
                </executions>
                <configuration>
                    <outputFormat>json</outputFormat>
                    <outputName>sbom</outputName>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

    <profiles>
        <!-- Security scan profile for CI/CD -->
        <profile>
            <id>security-scan</id>
            <build>
                <plugins>
                    <plugin>
                        <groupId>org.owasp</groupId>
                        <artifactId>dependency-check-maven</artifactId>
                        <executions>
                            <execution>
                                <phase>verify</phase>
                                <goals>
                                    <goal>check</goal>
                                </goals>
                            </execution>
                        </executions>
                    </plugin>
                </plugins>
            </build>
        </profile>
    </profiles>
</project>
```

**Continuous Monitoring Service**:

```java
package com.enterprise.security;

import org.springframework.boot.actuate.health.Health;
import org.springframework.boot.actuate.health.HealthIndicator;
import org.springframework.scheduling.annotation.Scheduled;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

import java.io.IOException;
import java.nio.file.Files;
import java.nio.file.Path;
import java.time.Instant;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;
import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;

@Component
public class DependencySecurityMonitor implements HealthIndicator {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(DependencySecurityMonitor.class);
    private static final Logger securityAuditLog = LoggerFactory.getLogger("SECURITY_AUDIT");

    private final Map<String, VulnerabilityStatus> vulnerabilityCache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();
    private volatile Instant lastScanTime = Instant.EPOCH;
    private volatile int criticalVulnCount = 0;
    private volatile int highVulnCount = 0;

    private final AlertService alertService;
    private final SbomService sbomService;

    public DependencySecurityMonitor(AlertService alertService, SbomService sbomService) {
        this.alertService = alertService;
        this.sbomService = sbomService;
    }

    @Override
    public Health health() {
        if (criticalVulnCount > 0) {
            return Health.down()
                .withDetail("critical_vulnerabilities", criticalVulnCount)
                .withDetail("high_vulnerabilities", highVulnCount)
                .withDetail("last_scan", lastScanTime.toString())
                .withDetail("action_required", "IMMEDIATE_PATCHING")
                .build();
        } else if (highVulnCount > 0) {
            return Health.status("DEGRADED")
                .withDetail("high_vulnerabilities", highVulnCount)
                .withDetail("last_scan", lastScanTime.toString())
                .build();
        }
        return Health.up()
            .withDetail("last_scan", lastScanTime.toString())
            .withDetail("status", "NO_KNOWN_VULNERABILITIES")
            .build();
    }

    @Scheduled(cron = "0 0 */4 * * *") // Every 4 hours
    public void scheduledVulnerabilityScan() {
        performVulnerabilityScan();
    }

    public void performVulnerabilityScan() {
        logger.info("Starting scheduled dependency vulnerability scan");
        securityAuditLog.info("event=DEPENDENCY_SCAN_START timestamp={}", Instant.now());

        try {
            List<Vulnerability> vulnerabilities = scanDependencies();
            processVulnerabilities(vulnerabilities);
            lastScanTime = Instant.now();

            securityAuditLog.info(
                "event=DEPENDENCY_SCAN_COMPLETE critical={} high={} timestamp={}",
                criticalVulnCount, highVulnCount, lastScanTime
            );

        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error("Vulnerability scan failed", e);
            securityAuditLog.error("event=DEPENDENCY_SCAN_FAILED error={}", e.getMessage());
            alertService.sendAlert(AlertLevel.HIGH, "Vulnerability scan failed: " + e.getMessage());
        }
    }

    private List<Vulnerability> scanDependencies() throws IOException {
        // Parse SBOM and check against vulnerability databases
        Path sbomPath = Path.of("target/sbom.json");
        if (!Files.exists(sbomPath)) {
            throw new IOException("SBOM not found - run 'mvn package' first");
        }
        return sbomService.checkVulnerabilities(sbomPath);
    }

    private void processVulnerabilities(List<Vulnerability> vulnerabilities) {
        int newCritical = 0;
        int newHigh = 0;

        for (Vulnerability vuln : vulnerabilities) {
            VulnerabilityStatus existing = vulnerabilityCache.get(vuln.getCveId());

            if (existing == null) {
                // New vulnerability detected
                securityAuditLog.warn(
                    "event=NEW_VULNERABILITY_DETECTED cve={} severity={} package={} version={}",
                    vuln.getCveId(), vuln.getSeverity(), 
                    vuln.getPackageName(), vuln.getVersion()
                );

                if (vuln.getSeverity() == Severity.CRITICAL) {
                    alertService.sendAlert(
                        AlertLevel.CRITICAL,
                        String.format("CRITICAL CVE detected: %s in %s:%s - Immediate action required",
                            vuln.getCveId(), vuln.getPackageName(), vuln.getVersion())
                    );
                }

                vulnerabilityCache.put(vuln.getCveId(), new VulnerabilityStatus(vuln, Instant.now()));
            }

            if (vuln.getSeverity() == Severity.CRITICAL) newCritical++;
            if (vuln.getSeverity() == Severity.HIGH) newHigh++;
        }

        this.criticalVulnCount = newCritical;
        this.highVulnCount = newHigh;
    }

    public record VulnerabilityStatus(Vulnerability vulnerability, Instant detectedAt) {}
    public record Vulnerability(String cveId, Severity severity, String packageName, 
                                String version, String fixedVersion) {
        public String getCveId() { return cveId; }
        public Severity getSeverity() { return severity; }
        public String getPackageName() { return packageName; }
        public String getVersion() { return version; }
    }
    public enum Severity { CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW }
    public enum AlertLevel { CRITICAL, HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW }
}
```

**Defense in Depth Layers**:

1. **Build-Time Enforcement** (Maven Enforcer):
```xml
<bannedDependencies>
    <excludes>
        <exclude>org.apache.logging.log4j:log4j-core:[,2.17.0)</exclude>
    </excludes>
</bannedDependencies>
```
Blocks builds containing known vulnerable versions.

2. **CI/CD Gate** (GitHub Actions):
```yaml
- name: OWASP Dependency Check
  run: mvn verify -Psecurity-scan
  env:
    NVD_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.NVD_API_KEY }}

- name: Upload SARIF to GitHub Security
  uses: github/codeql-action/upload-sarif@v2
  with:
    sarif_file: target/dependency-check-report.sarif
```

3. **Runtime Monitoring** (Health endpoint exposes vulnerability status for alerting systems)

**Additional Protections**:
- **SBOM Generation**: CycloneDX creates machine-readable inventory of all dependencies for supply chain transparency
- **Dependency Lockfile**: Use `maven-lockfile-plugin` or switch to Gradle with `--write-locks` to prevent dependency confusion attacks
- **Private Registry**: Use Artifactory or Nexus with vulnerability scanning to block risky packages before they enter your build
- **Automated PRs**: Integrate Dependabot or Renovate to automatically propose dependency updates with security context
- **Emergency Response Playbook**: Documented process for rapid patching when zero-days like Log4Shell are announced

Be extremely careful when using URL-based file fetching libraries. The popular `go-getter` library had critical vulnerabilities (CVE-2024-3817, CVE-2024-6257) that allowed remote code execution through crafted URLs.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"os"

	getter "github.com/hashicorp/go-getter" // v1.7.3 - VULNERABLE
)

func downloadArtifact(sourceURL string, destPath string) error {
	// DANGEROUS: Using outdated go-getter without URL validation
	// Vulnerable to path traversal and command injection
	client := &getter.Client{
		Src:  sourceURL,  // User-controlled URL
		Dst:  destPath,
		Mode: getter.ClientModeAny,
	}

	err := client.Get()
	if err != nil {
		return fmt.Errorf("failed to download: %w", err)
	}

	fmt.Printf("Downloaded %s to %s\n", sourceURL, destPath)
	return nil
}

func main() {
