Dependency management is one of the most critical security concerns in PHP applications. The 2023 Ghostscript vulnerability (CVE-2023-36664) affected numerous PHP applications that processed images, allowing remote code execution. Many PHP applications remain vulnerable because developers don't regularly audit their dependencies.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
